1
00:00:06,395 --> 00:00:09,535
几个世纪以来，我们研究了各个不同种类的物种。

2
00:00:09,540 --> 00:00:11,840
栖息在这个星球上的各种各样的物种，以了解

3
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:15,240
大自然的动力学是如何运作的。

4
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:20,935
世界各地数以千计的机构和人们都在

5
00:00:20,935 --> 00:00:24,045
努力产生知识，并通过

6
00:00:24,045 --> 00:00:26,925
数以百万计的发布使其可见，

7
00:00:26,925 --> 00:00:30,940
我们现在只需输入“生物多样性”这个词就可以找到这些知识。

8
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:36,840
所有这些信息背后的大部分数据

9
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:39,840
都是分散的，不太容易获取。

10
00:00:40,580 --> 00:00:43,955
当数据向公众开放时，这些数据更有价值

11
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:46,160
用于分析、使用和再利用

12
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:49,360
是知识创新和提高认识的必要基础

13
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:53,900
你能想象会有多少知识产生吗？

14
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:57,160
如果能有更多的人发现并使用这些数据

15
00:00:57,160 --> 00:00:59,500
用系统、开放的方式？

16
00:01:00,980 --> 00:01:04,540
全球生物多样性信息网络（Global Biodiversity Information Facility, GBIF）

17
00:01:04,540 --> 00:01:07,340
GBIF是一个由政府机构和非政府组织形成的平台

18
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:09,660
进行数据发布

19
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,280
并与全球用户进行分享

20
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,680
提供生物多样性相关的数据和资讯

21
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:17,740
在线提供给研究人员和公众使用

22
00:01:17,740 --> 00:01:19,740
无论身在何处

23
00:01:21,220 --> 00:01:23,100
In response to recommendations

24
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:25,320
from international agreements and conventions,

25
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:28,720
GBIF网络有几十个国家会员

26
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:30,760
近2000个发布者

27
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:34,720
bringing together a global scale data infrastructure for the natural world

28
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,520
that informs the sustainable use of biodiversity

29
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:40,680
and contributes to improving people’s quality of life.

30
00:01:45,420 --> 00:01:47,800
GBIF可以让您共享您所获得的数据

31
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:51,600
组织、标准化和发布

32
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:56,600
用于科学研究、教育和决策

33
00:01:56,600 --> 00:02:00,060
and expanding the knowledge we have about our environment.

34
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:04,635
Data publishers can choose the type of use and attribution

35
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,340
that they want for their data

36
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:09,680
and receive public recognition for their contributions.

37
00:02:11,460 --> 00:02:13,840
GBIF also makes it possible

38
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,740
for any citizen of the world, including you,

39
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:19,000
to access all the free and open data

40
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,760
published through the network’s data portals.

41
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:26,200
The nodes from each one of the participating countries

42
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,480
advise and work with organizations

43
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:31,200
through all phases of the data publishing process

44
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:33,900
to guarantee high-quality data, that are open and accessible.

45
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:38,300
We want you to be part of GBIF,

46
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:42,080
so that together we can build a sustainable future

47
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:45,080
in which biodiversity information is free and universally available

48
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:47,240
to science and society.

49
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:51,200
To learn more about how to become part of

50
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:54,720
this global biodiversity network,

51
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:58,900
访问www.gbif.org。

